# RougeShool Unity Development Rules

## Core Principles (SOLID)
- **Single Responsibility**: One class, one reason to change
- **Open-Closed**: Open for extension, closed for modification
- **Dependency Inversion**: Depend on interfaces, not concrete classes

## Unity Architecture
- **DI Pattern**: Use Zenject DI (NO singleton pattern)
- **Animation**: DOTween Pro only (AnimationSystem is deprecated)
- **Event-Driven**: NO Update() method - use event-based approach
- **Performance**: Object pooling required, GC pressure < 1KB/frame

## Korean Localization Standard
- All comments, logs, Inspector labels in Korean
- Required attributes: `[Header("전투 설정")]`, `[Tooltip("플레이어 체력")]`
- XML documentation in Korean for public APIs

## Code Quality
- Null safety: All public methods must validate parameters
- Exception handling: Try-catch with GameLogger.LogError
- Logging: Use GameLogger with appropriate categories

## Strict Prohibitions
- ❌ AnimationSystem references
- ❌ Singleton pattern (use Zenject)
- ❌ Update() methods
- ❌ FindObjectOfType in Update/FixedUpdate
- ❌ Duplicate functionality
- ❌ Example/dummy code generation
- ❌ Game-specific reference comments (e.g., "Slay the Spire style", "League of Legends system")
- ❌ AI-related comments (e.g., "AI generated", "Created by AI", "AI助手生成")
- ❌ Implementation hints in comments (e.g., "TODO: implement later", "This is just a placeholder")
- ❌ Change notification comments (e.g., "수정됨", "추가됨", "변경됨", "FIXED", "ADDED", "CHANGED", "Modified", "Updated here")
- ❌ Explanatory comments for user (e.g., "이 부분을 수정했습니다", "여기에 null 체크 추가", "성능 개선을 위해 변경")

## Workflow (AI Code Generation)
1. Search existing code first (codebase_search → grep → read_file)
2. Evaluate reusability before creating new code
3. Verify compilation (0 warnings, 0 errors)
4. Ensure Korean logging and XML documentation
